    "5": {
      "label": "Tier 5 drop __handlers fast path",
      "summary": "Compiler stops emitting __handlers; runtime drops the per-variant dispatch + _handleMsg. Saved 1,423 bytes uncompressed (1.2 kB gz) BUT caused 23-89% perf regressions on keyed-each operations (swap +89%, select +87%, remove +37%, update-10th +23%) per `pnpm bench`. __handlers' `method` discriminator dispatched to specialized reconcile paths (reconcileItems/reconcileClear/reconcileRemove/reconcileChanged) that the generic reconcile() can't match. Reverted — bundle savings not worth the perf cost.",
      "measuredUncompressed": 36026,
      "measuredGzipped": 11541,
      "measuredBrotli": 10192,
      "deltaVsBaseline": {
        "uncompressed": -7391,
        "gzipped": -1938,
